Megaton looked back and forth from Darkfate to Drillbit, he wasn&#39;t quite
sure exactly who was in charge. &quot;The news I bring is good for everybody
except our enemies. The part dragon-TRex- robot said watching his subjects.

Darkmouse growls, looking up at Megaton and showing no fear. &quot;I&#39;d
watch yourself if I were you. These are my friends you&#39;re around.&quot;

The 14 foot bot scoffed at the mouses statement about having friends. &quot;There
are no friends in wartime Mouse, We have only temporary conveniences when
thier needed.&quot; He knew that he had the right idea because the way war works
isn&#39;t friendly.

:::Starscream:::

::He had gotten over the shock of seeing Megaton and realized that if
he is joining them, They might as well be on friendlier terms::
Starscream: It seems we will be allies from now on.  What do you say
we let bygones be bygones?

Megaton watched Starscreams actions more than listened to his words, he
seemed sincere but as the old one often did could be hiding something. He
sensed an awkward feeling, like someone stepping on his grave (Since
Starscream tossed Megatron out of the ship in the movie it&#39;s reasonable.)
The joys of war were presenting themselves, first he was trying to destroy
Starscream, now they were allies. &quot;I agree. We are no longer at each others
backs so we can agree.&quot;

::DrillBit::

He wispered to StarScream, &quot;We will except him for now, but keep an
optic on him. The second we have a good reason, we turn him into scrap.&quot;
He then turned back to Megaton.
&quot;Do not speak to my officers that way, please,&quot; he said, refering to
Dark Mouse.

&quot;As you wish, I was not aware that you made her an officer, Megatrons files
listed her as just another sacrifice- I mean soldier to fight for the
Predacon cause.&quot; The mutant minced his words to piss off his new associates.
He wanted thier full attention on the enemy at hand and he knew he had it
even though he knew that none of the Preds he&#39;d encountered  trusted any of
his intentions. Darkmouse was seemong a little overconfident due to the
comment so Megaton fealt that he had to put her back in the right place.

&quot;Don&#39;t get cocky little one, even though you are high in rank you could
still easily be placed at the bottom of the food chain.

Get to the point, Megaton! If you want to continue to beat around the
bush, then go take a swim in the lava! Now tell us what you came to
tell.&quot;
He calmed himself, and his tone with the last sentance.
He would stand up for his troops. They were family to him. Megaton
wasn&#39;t going to come into their home, and push them around.

Megatons focus again presented itself to Drillbit. &quot;My point is that I have
access to the other Predacon base, and a strategy that would allow us to
destroy the other faction. Megaton smiled knowing that deciept and trust
were opposites in the Predacon dictionary. &quot;If you will listen to my ideas
and follow my directions we will eliminate any opposition.&quot;

Several troops of Darkfate were arriving to see what&#39;s going on.
Darkfate felt the tention in the Black Fortress.  His four snakes
were ready and hissing around the body of their master.

&quot;Of course that Megaton, won&#39;t have by now any intention to fight&quot;
said the dragon &quot;it&#39;s not wise annoy a Dragon in his own lair... &quot; he
added &quot;What are those important news Megaton?&quot;

Megaton stayed calm and collected as the reinforcements arrived. In his mind
he was invinceable and this group would hardly be a challenge. Darkfate
spoke,  &quot;Of course that Megaton, won&#39;t have by now any intention to fight&quot;
said the dragon &quot;it&#39;s not wise annoy a Dragon in his own lair... &quot; he added
&quot;What are those important news Megaton?&quot;

Megaton took a smug act into his actions. &quot;It is unwise to annoy a dragon in
any lair.&quot; He wanted every bot to know who he feared. He feared no one.











